Here are the essential skills needed for a sports betting automated agent:

Data & Analytics
- Real-time odds scraping and aggregation across multiple bookmakers
- Historical data mining and statistical modeling
- Probability calculation and expected value (EV) identification
- Line movement tracking and sharp money detection

Technical Infrastructure
- Low-latency API integrations with betting exchanges and sports data feeds
- Automated bet placement with error handling and retry logic
- Scalable architecture for handling high-frequency data streams
- Secure credential management and fund handling protocols

Risk Management
- Bankroll management algorithms (Kelly criterion, unit sizing)
- Diversification across sports, leagues, and bet types
- Exposure monitoring and correlation risk assessment
- Automated stop-losses and cool-down triggers

Market Intelligence
- Arbitrage and positive EV opportunity detection
- Steam chasing and reverse line movement analysis
- Weather, injury, and lineup impact modeling
- Closing line value (CLV) tracking for performance validation

Compliance & Operations
- Multi-jurisdiction regulatory awareness and geolocation handling
- Account health monitoring (avoiding limits/bans)
- Audit trails and reporting for tax/legal requirements
- Fraud detection and anomalous pattern recognition

Machine Learning (Optional but Advanced)
- Predictive modeling for game outcomes and player props
- Natural language processing for news/sentiment analysis
- Reinforcement learning for dynamic stake optimization
